        },
        "text": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Nothing sits in inventory. Each piece is made to order using lost-wax casting — the same technique goldsmiths have used since 3000 BCE. Molten 14k gold at 1,030°C flows into a plaster mold, capturing every organic detail the designer carved by hand.</p><p>After casting, each piece is filed, sanded through progressively finer grits, and polished by hand. Stones are set individually, bezels pushed by feel. The slightly uneven texture, the organically imperfect bezel — these are the maker's signature, embedded in every piece.</p><p>This means a 3–4 week production time. But it also means your piece carries the intention of being made just for this moment in your life.</p>",
            "text_font_class": "fs-body-100"
          }
        }
