          "settings": {
            "title": "Sterling Silver — The Canvas",
            "heading_tag": "h2",
            "heading_font_class": "fs-heading-2-base"
          }
        },
        "text": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Sterling silver (92.5% pure silver, 7.5% copper) isn't just cheaper gold — it's chosen for what it does that gold cannot. Silver has the highest reflectivity of any metal. When enamel is applied over silver, colors appear more vivid and luminous than over any other surface. The silver acts as a mirror behind the glass, amplifying color depth. For the bold, chromatic energy of Draped in Time, no other metal would work.</p>",
            "text_font_class": "fs-body-100"
          }
        }
      },
